laboratory_examinations.findings: 1.8 x 2.7 cm hypodense lesion within the hepatic dome in segment VIII, which may represent a hemangioma. 1.6 x 1.8 cm right hepatic lobe hyperdensity may represent a flash filling hemangioma. The appendix is dilated measuring 8 mm with hyperemia of the appendix wall and adjacent fat stranding noted. An appendicolith is also present at the appendix base.
